org.apache.hive.hcatalog.templeton.tool

Class LaunchMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper<org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable,org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text>
      • org.apache.hive.hcatalog.templeton.tool.LaunchMapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JobSubmissionConstants

    @InterfaceAudience.Private
public class LaunchMapper
extends org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper<org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable,org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text>
implements JobSubmissionConstants
    Note that this class is used in a different JVM than WebHCat server. Thus it should not call any classes not available on every node in the cluster (outside webhcat jar). TempletonControllerJob#run() calls Job.setJarByClass(LaunchMapper.class) which causes webhcat jar to be shipped to target node, but not it's transitive closure. Long term we need to clean up this separation and create a separate jar to ship so that the dependencies are clear. (This used to be an inner class of TempletonControllerJob)
